      "summary": ": Rāapa/Wednesday Mid Morning Update - The snow conditions are superb out there! The Saddlle is skiing and riding lovely and there is lots of fun to be had in the Home Basin. The sun is shining, the view is on point. Come on up! Skiing/riding should continue to be excellent up in the Saddle, with the best of the chalky goodness it in the gullies, humps and hollows. The grooming is in the Home Basin, with Triple Treat, Upper Main St and Beginner Platter all dressed up in fresh corduroy. Home Basin - Open Saddle Basin - Open Matukituki Basin - Closed Summit Slopes - Open Motatapu Chutes - Closed Sundance - Closed Backcountry Access - Open Skinning Access - Open",
